{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀποδῐδράσκω</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>ἀποδιδρήσκω</b>, <i>future</i> -δράσομαι, <i>Ionic dialect</i> -δρήσομαι: <i>perfect</i> <b>-δέδρᾱκα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Σαμία” 143, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.199 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἀπέδραν, <i>Ionic dialect</i> -έδρην, <i>optative</i> ἀποδραίην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 927, _imperative_ ἀπόδρᾱθι 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 1.90\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], <i>infinitive</i> ἀποδρᾶναι, <i>Ionic dialect</i> -δρῆναι, <i>participle</i> ἀποδράς—the only form found in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; the other tenses in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>perfect</i> <i>participle</i> ἀποδεδρακότες[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 6.4.8\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>run away, escape</b> or <b>flee from,</b> especially <b>by stealth,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (never in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”), ἐκ νηὸς ἀποδράς 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.65; νηὸς ἀ. 17.516; ἀ. ἐκ τῆς Σάμου 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.148; ἐς Σάμον 4.43; ἐπὶ θάλασσαν 6.2; ἀποδρᾶσα ᾤχετο 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.125, compare 4.17, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 196, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 203d \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of runaway slaves, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.4.8 (ἀποδρᾶναι τὸ ἀναχωρήσαντά τινα εὔδηλον εἶναι ὅπου ἐστίν, ἀποφεύγειν δὲ τὸ μὴ δύνασθαι ἐπιληφθῆναι Ammon. p.19 V.); σώματα ἀποδράντα “IG” 22.584 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of soldiers, <b>desert,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.6.34\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀποδιδράσκοντα μὴ δύνασθαι ἀποδρᾶναι <b>attempting to escape</b> not to be able <b>to escape,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 317a, compare 310c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>flee, shun,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.182, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 234, etc.; ἀπέδρασαν αὐτόν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.128\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>evade,</b> τὸν νόμον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1270b35; οὐκ ἀπέδρα τὴν στρατείαν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.165\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὅτε.. τὸ σὸν ὄμμ᾽ ἀπέδραν (<i>poetry</i> for ἀπέδρασαν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 167.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —Rare in Trag. (Cf. Sanskrit δρᾱτι 'run'.)","strongNumber":"G6424","accentedUnicode":"ἀποδιδράσκω","shortDef":"to run away","mediumDef":"to run away","stepGloss":"to run away","stepTransliteration":"apodidraskō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}